<subSubSection id="FA05A4D8E2E0942F4E3E63BC5F6F340C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="B907CF83972767F4E604553D6BDFFD31" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2E4B090C0389AB1E10FAB33245028AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very vigorous liana-like perennial to 5 m; stems relatively stout, thinly pilose with long white hairs, spinulose with short triangular spines on angles. Leaves petiolate, 9-11 
<normalizedToken id="12D26F0AA3CAEE171E90D2520A26CC5A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-10 cm, ovate, base cordate with rounded auricles, apex acute to shortly mucronate, margin entire, adaxially green, glabrous, abaxially paler, veins pilose and highlighted with whitish hairs, intercostal regions glabrous; petioles 5-9 cm, thinly pilose. Inflorescence of long-pedunculate, lax, compound cymes comprising 5-10 flowers; primary peduncles very long, 17-21 cm, thinly pilose and with a few scattered stalked glands and spinules; secondary peduncles 3-3.5 cm, pilose; tertiary peduncles 2-3 cm; bracteoles 1.5 
<normalizedToken id="7E787C439F4B1FDB830AB41AC5D03A94" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5 mm, oblong, caducous; pedicels 12-23 mm, densely white-pilose, bearded below flower; outer sepals 10-11 
<normalizedToken id="62AC561A7930BE0DBE6A2BCCF2A85DB3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7 mm, ovate, obtuse to retuse, dark green when fresh, pubescent at centre near base, glabrous upwards and at margins, the scarious margins thin; inner sepals 10-11 
<normalizedToken id="7CAAD8BA5514A8622ABEEA143D0D2820" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8 mm, broadly elliptic, glabrous except near base, scarious margins broad; corolla 7.5-9 cm long, gradually widened from base, pink, in bud pubescent, limb c. 5 cm diam., undulate to weakly lobed. Capsules and seeds not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
